<li id="cite_note-1"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-1">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">A <i>formal language</i> is a set of words, i.e. finite strings of letters or symbols. The inventory from which these letters are taken is the <i>alphabet</i> through which the language is defined. A formal language is often defined by means of a <a href="Formal_grammar" title="Formal grammar">formal grammar</a>, but it does not describe their <a href="Semantics" title="Semantics">semantics</a> (i.e., what they mean)</span></li>
